I have a daisy on my toe.
It is not real. It does not grow.
It's just a tattoo of a flower,
So I'll look neat taking a shower.
It's on the second toe of my left foot,
A stem and flower, but there's no root
--- because that wouldn't look good !
It's just a daisy on my toe.
My left foot loves my right foot so !

messages.subject: Re: [unschoolingbasics] foot tattoo
messages.msgSnippet: I don t, but I have heard it is more painful. The skin is thinner there and nerves closer to the surface, you re closer to bone (making it more painful), etc.
messages.messageBody:
I don't, but I have heard it is more painful. The skin is thinner
there and nerves closer to the surface, you're closer to bone (making
it more painful), etc.

A board I belong to just discussed this topic, actually. I can send a
link to that if you want, it's a public board.

Tami
